Q. When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work local?
A. when i want to share my work or work with a person outside my intranet or want to backup my work.

Q. Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git automatically stay up-to-date with your
   remote repository?
A. we dont want changes to be done without verifying thier correctness. if someone else has a permission to modify
   then the main user will first verify it then add the changes

Q. Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches. When would you use one instead of another?
A. fork - cloning a repository from one github account to another.
   clone - is to copy a repository from github to your local computer.
   branches - they are created on a repository either on github or local computer to work on either a new
   feature paralley or do something experimental and still have a working copy of project(master)

Q. What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote stored locally?
A. Git can decide whether to make a fast forward merge , or a a conflict is aring then we have to merge manually.
